/-
  Data.PDF.Content.TexGlyphList — the TeX glyph list

  Ports `Pdf.Content.TexGlyphList` from Hackage's `pdf-toolbox-content`
  (https://github.com/Yuras/pdf-toolbox, `content/lib/Pdf/Content/TexGlyphList.hs`,
  fetched from
  `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Yuras/pdf-toolbox/master/content/lib/Pdf/Content/TexGlyphList.hs`),
  module 5 of the `pdf-toolbox-content` import documented in
  `docs/imports/PdfToolboxContent/dependencies.md`.

  A supplementary glyph-name table (~284 entries) covering glyph names used
  by TeX fonts that are absent from the Adobe Glyph List
  (`Data.PDF.Content.GlyphList`). Like that module, this is pure data with no
  behaviour to port.

  ## Design

  Same representation choice as `Data.PDF.Content.GlyphList`:
  `Std.HashMap Data.ByteString Char` in place of upstream's
  `Map ByteString Char`. Upstream's table has no duplicate keys, so no
  `.reverse` trick is needed.
-/
